</table>

<!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<h2 id="sse">18. SSE Events — Real-Time Streaming to Browser</h2>
<p>The browser connects to the backend via <code>EventSource</code> (Server-Sent Events). As the agent runs, events stream live so the user sees results appear in real time.</p>
<table>
  <tr><th>Event name</th><th>When it fires</th><th>Key data</th></tr>
  <tr><td><code>status</code></td><td>Every progress step</td><td>step (searching/fetching/pacing/filtering/ai_scoring), message, progress %</td></tr>
  <tr><td><code>search_done</code></td><td>After each keyword search</td><td>query, found count, new handles count</td></tr>
  <tr><td><code>account</code></td><td>After each account is scored and saved</td><td>Full account object with all scores, type, track, contact info</td></tr>
  <tr><td><code>fetch_error</code></td><td>When a profile fetch fails</td><td>handle, HTTP status code, error message</td></tr>
  <tr><td><code>quota_exhausted</code></td><td>After 3 consecutive 429s</td><td>Message explaining quota is used up and when it resets</td></tr>
  <tr><td><code>complete</code></td><td>When the run finishes</td><td>accounts added, accounts updated, error count, run ID</td></tr>
</table>

<!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<h2 id="direct">19. Direct Handle Fetch — Friend's Influencer List</h2>
<p>The friend's database contains 42 pre-curated influencer handles (e.g. @swyx, @karpathy, @ggerganov). These are fetched <strong>directly</strong> at the end of every run — no keyword search step needed.</p>
<ul>
  <li>Same minimum bar validation applies (followers, tweets, name, bio checks)</li>
  <li>Same AI batch scoring applies (only new handles)</li>
  <li>Results saved to OUR Turso database only — friend's DB is never written to</li>
  <li>SSE events emitted with <code>source: 'friend_list'</code> in the account data</li>
</ul>

<!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<h2 id="quota">20. Quota Exhaustion — When the API Runs Out</h2>
<p>RapidAPI keys have monthly request limits. When quota runs out:</p>
<ol>
  <li>API returns HTTP 429 (Too Many Requests)</li>
  <li>That key enters a 75-second cooldown</li>
  <li>Other key takes over immediately</li>
  <li>If both keys get 429 back-to-back three times → quota is exhausted</li>
  <li>System stops the run gracefully — saves all data collected so far</li>
  <li>Emits <code>quota_exhausted</code> SSE event with explanation</li>
  <li>Quota resets at midnight UTC</li>
</ol>
<div class="box-gold">
  <strong>How to avoid hitting quota:</strong> Run the agent fewer times per month. The auto-cron (once per month on the 1st) is the intended cadence. Manual runs during the month burn through quota faster.
</div>

<!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<h2 id="endpoints">21. All API Endpoints</h2>
<table>
  <tr><th>Method</th><th>Path</th><th>Auth</th><th>What it does</th></tr>
  <tr><td>GET</td><td>/api/health</td><td>Public</td><td>Backend status, key availability, DB connection</td></tr>
  <tr><td>POST</td><td>/api/auth/login</td><td>Public</td><td>Email + password → returns JWT token (7-day expiry)</td></tr>
  <tr><td>GET</td><td>/api/run-demo</td><td>JWT</td><td>SSE stream — starts the full agent pipeline</td></tr>
  <tr><td>GET</td><td>/api/accounts</td><td>JWT</td><td>All accounts with optional filters (track, tier, min_score, limit)</td></tr>
  <tr><td>GET</td><td>/api/accounts/influencers</td><td>JWT</td><td>Track A accounts only (collab pipeline)</td></tr>
  <tr><td>GET</td><td>/api/accounts/pr-pages</td><td>JWT</td><td>Track B accounts only (ads audience)</td></tr>
  <tr><td>GET</td><td>/api/accounts/:handle</td><td>JWT</td><td>Single account by handle</td></tr>
  <tr><td>GET</td><td>/api/keywords</td><td>JWT</td><td>Own keyword list from DB</td></tr>
  <tr><td>POST</td><td>/api/keywords</td><td>JWT</td><td>Add new keyword to own list</td></tr>
  <tr><td>PATCH</td><td>/api/keywords/:id</td><td>JWT</td><td>Toggle keyword active/inactive</td></tr>
  <tr><td>DELETE</td><td>/api/keywords/:id</td><td>JWT</td><td>Remove keyword from own list</td></tr>
  <tr><td>GET</td><td>/api/keywords/friend</td><td>JWT</td><td>View friend's keywords (read-only — never modifiable)</td></tr>
  <tr><td>GET</td><td>/api/dashboard/stats</td><td>JWT</td><td>KPI totals, account type/tier breakdown, top 10 accounts, run history</td></tr>
  <tr><td>GET</td><td>/api/settings</td><td>JWT</td><td>Config status (key presence — no actual key values ever returned)</td></tr>
  <tr><td>POST</td><td>/api/settings/test-openrouter</td><td>JWT</td><td>Test AI connection with a live call</td></tr>
  <tr><td>POST</td><td>/api/settings/keys/test</td><td>JWT</td><td>Test both RapidAPI keys with a live call</td></tr>
  <tr><td>GET</td><td>/api/settings/test-friend-db</td><td>JWT</td><td>Test read connection to friend's database</td></tr>
  <tr><td>PATCH</td><td>/api/settings/:key</td><td>JWT</td><td>Update non-sensitive config (e.g. auto_run_enabled)</td></tr>
</table>

<!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<h2 id="security">22. Security</h2>
<table>
  <tr><th>Measure</th><th>Details</th></tr>
  <tr><td>JWT authentication</td><td>All data endpoints require a Bearer token. 7-day expiry.</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Password hashing</td><td>bcrypt with 12 salt rounds — passwords never stored in plain text.</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Registration disabled</td><td>Public /register endpoint returns 403. Admin account is created from .env on startup only.</td></tr>
  <tr><td>API keys in .env</td><td>All keys (RapidAPI, OpenRouter, Turso, JWT secret) live in backend/.env only. Never in frontend code, never in any API response.</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Rate limiting</td><td>20 auth attempts per 15 minutes. 120 API calls per minute. express-rate-limit.</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Security headers</td><td>Helmet.js — X-Content-Type-Options, X-Frame-Options, X-XSS-Protection.</td></tr>
  <tr><td>CORS</td><td>Restricted to configured ALLOWED_ORIGINS + *.vercel.app preview URLs only.</td></tr>
  <tr><td>SSE authentication</td><td>Token passed via _token query param (EventSource API cannot send custom headers).</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Settings page</td><td>Never returns raw key values — only shows "set/not set" status and masked previews.</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Friend DB</td><td>Only SELECT queries ever run against the friend's database. INSERT/UPDATE/DELETE are architecturally impossible.</td></tr>
</table>

<!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<h2 id="stack">23. Tech Stack &amp; Deployment</h2>
<table>
  <tr><th>Layer</th><th>Technology</th><th>URL / Notes</th></tr>
  <tr><td>Frontend</td><td>React 18 + Vite 5 + React Router v6</td><td>https://pr-x-agent.vercel.app — auto-deploys on git push</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Backend</td><td>Node.js 22 + Express 4</td><td>https://pr-x-agent.onrender.com — auto-deploys on git push</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Own Database</td><td>Turso (libSQL / SQLite edge)</td><td>Free tier — 5 tables, persistent storage</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Friend Database</td><td>Turso (read-only connection)</td><td>1,506 keywords + 42 handles, never written to</td></tr>
  <tr><td>AI Scoring</td><td>OpenRouter → Claude Opus 4.5</td><td>Batch size 6, fallback to keyword heuristics if unavailable</td></tr>
  <tr><td>X Data</td><td>RapidAPI twitter-api45</td><td>2 keys, 6 RPM each, proactive rate limiter</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Scheduler</td><td>node-cron</td><td>Runs inside the Render backend — 1st of month, 02:00 UTC</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Auth</td><td>JWT + bcryptjs</td><td>Stateless — works across split Render/Vercel deployment</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Repository</td><td>GitHub</td><td>github.com/Yathukrishnan/PR_X_AGENT</td></tr>
</table>

<!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<h2 id="costs">24. Costs</h2>
<table>
  <tr><th>Service</th><th>Estimated Monthly Cost</th><th>Notes</th></tr>
  <tr><td>RapidAPI (twitter-api45)</td><td>$0 free tier / $10–50 paid</td><td>Free: 500 req/month. Need ~6,000/month for a full run (358 queries × ~17 profiles each)</td></tr>
  <tr><td>OpenRouter (Claude Opus 4.5)</td><td>~$1–3</td><td>~300 new accounts/run × batched at 6 = ~50 AI calls</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Turso</td><td>Free</td><td>Free tier: 500 databases, 9GB storage</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Render (backend)</td><td>Free / $7/month</td><td>Free tier spins down after inactivity. $7 for always-on</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Vercel (frontend)</td><td>Free</td><td>Hobby tier covers this project easily</td></tr>
  <tr><td><strong>Total</strong></td><td><strong>~$1–60/month</strong></td><td>Depends on RapidAPI plan chosen</td></tr>
</table>

